            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ECaleb%20was%20a%20man%20of%20unrelenting%20pursuit.%20His%20eyes%20had%20seen%20a%20mountain%2C%20and%20Moses%20had%20given%20him%20a%20promise.%20Although%20he%20was%20now%20eighty-five%20years%20old%2C%20his%20resolve%20and%20desire%20to%20possess%20the%20promise%20were%20undiminished.%20He%20said%20to%20Joshua%2C%20%22So%20I'm%20asking%20you%20to%20give%20me%20the%20hill%20country%20that%20the%20Lord%20promised%20me%22%20(Joshua%2014%3A12).%20Then%20this%20elderly%20man%20of%20faith%20promptly%20went%20in%20and%20drove%20out%20the%20giants%20who%20lived%20there!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EForty-five%20years%20of%20waiting%20did%20nothing%20to%20daunt%20this%20man's%20purposes%20in%20God.%20How%20often%20do%20we%20%22circle%20the%20mountain%22%20one%20time%20and%20then%20decide%20it%20is%20not%20the%20will%20of%20God%20for%20us%20to%20receive%20what%20we%20need%3F%20In%20many%20instances%20recorded%20in%20the%20Bible%2C%20people%20of%20faith%20had%20to%20persevere%20in%20order%20to%20receive%20the%20promise.%20For%20example%2C%20Elijah%20prayed%20seven%20times%20before%20he%20saw%20the%20cloud%20of%20rain%2C%20and%20Joshua%20marched%20seven%20days%20until%20the%20walls%20of%20Jericho%20toppled.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20the%20parable%20of%20the%20importuning%20widow%20(Luke%2018%3A5)%2C%20Jesus%20taught%20the%20importance%20of%20persistence.%20If%20an%20unjust%20judge%20would%20eventually%20grant%20the%20request%20of%20a%20persistent%20widow%2C%20how%20much%20more%20will%20a%20compassionate%20God%20answer%20the%20prayers%20of%20His%20righteous%20saints%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPursue%20your%20dream.%20And%20until%20the%20dream%20comes%20to%20pass%2C%20continue%20to%20proclaim%2C%20%22Give%20me%20this%20hill%20country!%22%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
