            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Joshua.13:1-14:15",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJoshua%2013%3A1-14%3A15%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_1%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJoshua%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Yet%20to%20Be%20Conquered%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Joshua%20was%20an%20old%20man%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20are%20growing%20old%2C%20and%20much%20land%20remains%20to%20be%20conquered.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_2%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20territory%20that%20remains%3A%20all%20the%20regions%20of%20the%20Philistines%20and%20the%20Geshurites%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_3%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20the%20larger%20territory%20of%20the%20Canaanites%2C%20extending%20from%20the%20stream%20of%20Shihor%20on%20the%20border%20of%20Egypt%2C%20northward%20to%20the%20boundary%20of%20Ekron.%20It%20includes%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20five%20Philistine%20rulers%20of%20Gaza%2C%20Ashdod%2C%20Ashkelon%2C%20Gath%2C%20and%20Ekron.%20The%20land%20of%20the%20Avvites%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_4%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3Ein%20the%20south%20also%20remains%20to%20be%20conquered.%20In%20the%20north%2C%20the%20following%20area%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20conquered%3A%20all%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Canaanites%2C%20including%20Mearah%20(which%20belongs%20to%20the%20Sidonians)%2C%20stretching%20northward%20to%20Aphek%20on%20the%20border%20of%20the%20Amorites%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_5%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Ethe%20land%20of%20the%20Gebalites%20and%20all%20of%20the%20Lebanon%20mountain%20area%20to%20the%20east%2C%20from%20Baal-gad%20below%20Mount%20Hermon%20to%20Lebo-hamath%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_6%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20all%20the%20hill%20country%20from%20Lebanon%20to%20Misrephoth-maim%2C%20including%20all%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Sidonians.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20myself%20will%20drive%20these%20people%20out%20of%20the%20land%20ahead%20of%20the%20Israelites.%20So%20be%20sure%20to%20give%20this%20land%20to%20Israel%20as%20a%20special%20possession%2C%20just%20as%20I%20have%20commanded%20you.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_7%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EInclude%20all%20this%20territory%20as%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20possession%20when%20you%20divide%20this%20land%20among%20the%20nine%20tribes%20and%20the%20half-tribe%20of%20Manasseh.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_8%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Divided%20East%20of%20the%20Jordan%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHalf%20the%20tribe%20of%20Manasseh%20and%20the%20tribes%20of%20Reuben%20and%20Gad%20had%20already%20received%20their%20grants%20of%20land%20on%20the%20east%20side%20of%20the%20Jordan%2C%20for%20Moses%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20had%20previously%20assigned%20this%20land%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_9%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20territory%20extended%20from%20Aroer%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20Arnon%20Gorge%20(including%20the%20town%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20gorge)%20to%20the%20plain%20beyond%20Medeba%2C%20as%20far%20as%20Dibon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_10%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20also%20included%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20King%20Sihon%20of%20the%20Amorites%2C%20who%20had%20reigned%20in%20Heshbon%2C%20and%20extended%20as%20far%20as%20the%20borders%20of%20Ammon.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_11%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20included%20Gilead%2C%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20kingdoms%20of%20Geshur%20and%20Maacah%2C%20all%20of%20Mount%20Hermon%2C%20all%20of%20Bashan%20as%20far%20as%20Salecah%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_12%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20all%20the%20territory%20of%20King%20Og%20of%20Bashan%2C%20who%20had%20reigned%20in%20Ashtaroth%20and%20Edrei.%20King%20Og%20was%20the%20last%20of%20the%20Rephaites%2C%20for%20Moses%20had%20attacked%20them%20and%20driven%20them%20out.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_13%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20Israelites%20failed%20to%20drive%20out%20the%20people%20of%20Geshur%20and%20Maacah%2C%20so%20they%20continue%20to%20live%20among%20the%20Israelites%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_14%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EAn%20Allotment%20for%20the%20Tribe%20of%20Levi%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20did%20not%20assign%20any%20allotment%20of%20land%20to%20the%20tribe%20of%20Levi.%20Instead%2C%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20promised%20them%2C%20their%20allotment%20came%20from%20the%20offerings%20burned%20on%20the%20altar%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_15%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20the%20Tribe%20of%20Reuben%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20had%20assigned%20the%20following%20area%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Reuben.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_16%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20territory%20extended%20from%20Aroer%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20Arnon%20Gorge%20(including%20the%20town%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20gorge)%20to%20the%20plain%20beyond%20Medeba.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_17%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20included%20Heshbon%20and%20the%20other%20towns%20on%20the%20plain%26%23x2014%3BDibon%2C%20Bamoth-baal%2C%20Beth-baal-meon%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_18%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EJahaz%2C%20Kedemoth%2C%20Mephaath%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_19%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EKiriathaim%2C%20Sibmah%2C%20Zereth-shahar%20on%20the%20hill%20above%20the%20valley%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_20%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EBeth-peor%2C%20the%20slopes%20of%20Pisgah%2C%20and%20Beth-jeshimoth.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_21%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20land%20of%20Reuben%20also%20included%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20the%20plain%20and%20the%20entire%20kingdom%20of%20Sihon.%20Sihon%20was%20the%20Amorite%20king%20who%20had%20reigned%20in%20Heshbon%20and%20was%20killed%20by%20Moses%20along%20with%20the%20leaders%20of%20Midian%26%23x2014%3BEvi%2C%20Rekem%2C%20Zur%2C%20Hur%2C%20and%20Reba%26%23x2014%3Bprinces%20living%20in%20the%20region%20who%20were%20allied%20with%20Sihon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_22%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Israelites%20had%20also%20killed%20Balaam%20son%20of%20Beor%2C%20who%20used%20magic%20to%20tell%20the%20future.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_23%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Jordan%20River%20marked%20the%20western%20boundary%20for%20the%20tribe%20of%20Reuben.%20The%20towns%20and%20their%20surrounding%20villages%20in%20this%20area%20were%20given%20as%20a%20homeland%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Reuben.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_24%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Land%20Given%20to%20the%20Tribe%20of%20Gad%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20had%20assigned%20the%20following%20area%20to%20the%20clans%20of%20the%20tribe%20of%20Gad.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_25%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20territory%20included%20Jazer%2C%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Gilead%2C%20and%20half%20of%20the%20land%20of%20Ammon%2C%20as%20far%20as%20the%20town%20of%20Aroer%20just%20west%20of%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A25%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20front%20of.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Rabbah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_26%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20extended%20from%20Heshbon%20to%20Ramath-mizpeh%20and%20Betonim%2C%20and%20from%20Mahanaim%20to%20the%20territory%20of%20Lo-debar.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A26%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ELi-debir%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20apparently%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Lo-debar%20(compare%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%209%3A4%3B%2017%3A27%3B%20Amos%206%3A13).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh_13_27%22%20bk%3D%22josh%22%20ch%3D%2213%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20valley%20were%20Beth-haram%2C%20Beth-nimrah%2C%20Succoth%2C%20Zaphon%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20kingdom%20of%20King%20Sihon%20of%20Heshbon.%20The%20western%20boundary%20ran%20along%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20extended%20as%20far%20north%20as%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20Sea%20of%20Galilee%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E13%3A27%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ESea%20of%20Kinnereth.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20then%20turned%20eastward.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22josh